WINTER SPRINGS, Fla. - One of six Winter Springs High School students who are accused of gang-raping a 16-year-old girl in the woods is no longer facing charges in the case.

Channel 9 learned that charges were dropped against Torreano Batton, who is 18 and was the only adult arrested.
